\begin{table}[p]
\centering
\caption{Classification of cancer therapies by structural
relationship to the escalation chain.}
\label{tab:therapy-classification}
\begin{tabular}{@{}>{\raggedright}p{4cm}>{\raggedright}p{3.5cm}>{\raggedright}p{7cm}>{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{6cm}@{}}
\toprule
Therapy & Category & Mechanism & Predicted durability \\
\midrule
Environmental remediation
 & Remove cause
 & Halts $\lambda_j$ degradation
 & Before ratchet only \\[4pt]
Pathogen eradication (\emph{H.~pylori}, HBV/HCV)
 & Remove cause
 & Halts inflammatory damage
 & Before ratchet only \\[4pt]
Imatinib (BCR-ABL)
 & Remove cause
 & Silences decoupling signal
 & Durable (decade+); fails in blast crisis \\[4pt]
ATRA in APL
 & Restore chain
 & Restores $\lambda_1$ (differentiation)
 & $>$90\% cure rate \\[4pt]
Anti-PD-1/PD-L1
 & Restore chain
 & Restores $\lambda_3^{\mathrm{immune}}$
 & Durable in subset (self-maintaining) \\[4pt]
Microenvironment normalization
 & Restore chain
 & Restores $\lambda_1$, $\lambda_2$
 & Durable if infrastructure restored \\[4pt]
Gap junction restoration \cite{Aasen2016}
 & Restore chain
 & Restores $\lambda_1$ (GJIC)
 & Predicted: suppresses malignancy \\[4pt]
Anti-estrogen, anti-HER2
 & Selection pressure
 & Targets coupling channel
 & Drives ratchet; resistance predicted \\[4pt]
Chemotherapy, radiation
 & Selection pressure
 & Non-specific cytoreduction
 & Resistance predicted ($\gamma > 0$) \\[4pt]
Surgery
 & Physical removal
 & Removes decoupled entity
 & Effective if localized \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\end{landscape}

